feels.name: Surprise
feels.quote: In the distance, a great white mass lazily rose, and rising higher and higher, and disentangling itself from the azure, at last gleamed before our prow like a snow-slide, new slid from the hills.

feels.name: Joy
feels.quote: Upon this, the seamen rushed to the yard-arms, as in swarming-time the bees rush to the boughs.

feels.name: Impatience
feels.quote: Some vague dissatisfaction, or impatience, or despair, seemed working in him; as if the sight of that dead body reminded him that Moby Dick was yet to be slain.

feels.name: Excitement
feels.quote: Flushed with conquest, betrayed an unusual but still good-natured excitement.

feels.name: Anger
feels.quote: Bress my soul, if I cook noder one,‚Äù he growled, angrily, turning round to depart.
